thread.title: Cross country: Grove sweeps to titles at Kenton
thread.title_full: Cross country: Grove sweeps to titles at Kenton

author: The Courier
title: Cross country: Grove sweeps to titles at Kenton
text:
Comment: 0 
KENTON — Columbus Grove’s Taylor Ellerbrock won the girls race, and Boone Brubaker was second in the boys race as Grove’s cross country teams swept the team titles Thursday at the Kenton Invitational at the Hardin County Fairgrounds. Ellerbrock led three Bulldogs in the top 10, with Macy McCluer finishing seventh and Leah Myerholtz ninth. The times in the girls race were not reported. Brubaker finished in 17:28.22 and also led three Grove runners in the top 10. Preston Brubaker was fifth (18:07.50) and Grant Mumaugh ninth (18:38.00). Grove’s girls scored 40 points to defeat Kenton (63) and Bellefontaine (67). Grove’s boys (47 points) defeated Benjamin Logan (53) and Bellefontaine (54). 
Kenton Invitational Boys Team Scores 1, Columbus Grove 47. 2, Benjamin Logan 53. 3, Bellefontaine 54. 4, Lima Bath 85. 5, Kenton 113. 6, Waynesfield-Goshen 177. 7, Lima Senior 184. 8, Triad 242. Girls Team Scores 1, Columbus Grove 40. 2, Kenton 63. 3, Bellefontaine 67. 4, Triad 82. 5, Lima Bath 99. 6, Benjamin Logan 144.
